column803: Drainage and flooding is a challenge, and all system have to work together to convey water. Underground drainage, open ditches, roadways, and bayous are engineered and synced to efficiently drain. If one out performs the other, conveyance is not optimized. In Houston, all new construction must be built 500 yr flood plain plus 2', and we have strict detention requirements,  which together, should help mitigate structure flooding. Houston Public works maintains underground drainage and some open ditches, while Harris County Flood Control maintains some open ditches and all bayous/rivers. Together, we manage the drainage system, and work very closely to sync and time projects to provide maximum value for the citizens. In general, we use data to ID and prioritize flood mitigation projects.
